<item>
            <title>[TIKA-358] Auto-detection of HTML fails with common auto-generated template</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-358</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a commonly generated HTML document format that fools the auto-detection code into classifying it as XML.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve attached one example of this, from &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.saveums.com/detect.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.saveums.com/detect.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then the XML parser barfs because there&apos;s a dangling comment at the end.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In all the cases I&apos;ve seen, the server returns the right mime-type (text/html), so perhaps this could be used to disambiguate.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
